d Prix Series regular season podium (dating to 2013) and 17th consecutive top-two finish in a Grand Prix regular season event (dating to 2014).\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 546, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At NHK this week, Chock and Bates can make a 25th career Grand Prix podium (including Grand Prix Finals) to extend their record for ice dancers.\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NHK\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.547597249762999e-12, \"text\": \"NHK\", \"types\": [\"Q737498\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NHK\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NHK\"}, {\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.115353579985839e-68, \"text\": \"Chock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\"}, {\"begin\": 576, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.040960927639849e-41, \"text\": \"Bates\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\"}, {\"begin\": 605, \"end\": 615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.66554341258417e-55, \"text\": \"Grand Prix\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If they do that, Chock and Bates will likely also qualify for the Grand Prix Final for a ninth time, also extending their ice dance record.\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.115353579985839e-68, \"text\": \"Chock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\"}, {\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.040960927639849e-41, \"text\": \"Bates\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\"}, {\"begin\": 759, \"end\": 769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.66554341258417e-55, \"text\": \"Grand Prix\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Grand Prix Series is figure skating's regular season circuit with one competition per week for six consecutive weeks each fall.\", \"from\": 834, \"to\": 965, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The world's top skaters compete in two events each.\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top six per discipline over the series qualify for December's Grand Prix Final, where all of the world's best skaters gather for the first time each season.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Grand Prix Final is often a preview of the following March's world championships.\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.66554341258417e-55, \"text\": \"Grand Prix\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ISU_Grand_Prix_of_Figure_Skating\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chock and Bates are clear favorites at NHK given the world's other top couples are competing the following two weeks for their second Grand Prix starts.\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1277, \"end\": 1282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.040960927639849e-41, \"text\": \"Bates\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\"}, {\"begin\": 1306, \"end\": 1309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NHK\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.547597249762999e-12, \"text\": \"NHK\", \"types\": [\"Q737498\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NHK\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NHK\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such as Brits Lilah Fear and Lewis Gibson, who won Skate America after Chock and Bates counted a fall in their rhythm dance.\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1544, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1449, \"end\": 1461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Gibson_(figure_skater)\", \"score\": 0.9659054179997993, \"rank\": 0.035294117647045, \"text\": \"Lewis Gibson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Gibson_(figure_skater)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_Gibson_(figure_skater)\"}, {\"begin\": 1501, \"end\": 1506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.040960927639849e-41, \"text\": \"Bates\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Bates\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, Chock and Bates' scores this week will be worth noting.\"